Package neureka.devices

Interface Storage<ValueType>

  • Type Parameters:
    ValueType -
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Device<ValueType>, FileHead<FinalType,​ValueType>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractBaseDevice, AbstractDevice, AbstractFileHead, DummyDevice, FileDevice, HostCPU, IDXHead, JPEGHead, OpenCLDevice
    public interface Storage<ValueType>
    This is an abstract interface which simply describes "a thing that stores tensors". Therefore the expected method signatures defining this abstract entity boil down to a "store" and a "restore" method. Classes like "OpenCLDevice" or "FileDevice" implement this interface indirectly (via the Device interface) because they are in essence also just entities that store tensors! Besides the "Device" interface this interface is also extended by the FileHead interface which is an internal component of the FileDevice architecture...
